	<td class="nopad" valign="top" width="85%">
		<table class="hide" cellspacing="1">
		<tr>
			<td class="print">
				Hi,<br />
So I have added a patch by the name of 569.patch for this issue.<br />
<br />
I have added two date fields for the Min and Max fields. And the Date Field is rendered in a mm/dd/YY format but is stored internally as the Linux Epoch Time in seconds using the same AdminUtil.PROP_FX_MAX_LIMIT and AdminUtil.PROP_FX_MIN_LIMIT params as it was previous, so this does not break any other functionality associated with the same.<br />
<br />
Also, I noticed, whenever a &quot;Text Field&quot; was selected, there were options to select different types of Text Fields like &quot;Paragraph&quot;, &quot;TextArea&quot;, &quot;Number&quot; , &quot;Date&quot;, and the other options like &quot;isDecimal&quot;, &quot;Length&quot;, &quot;Min&quot;, &quot;Max&quot; also. These options were not required for all the different types of TextFields, so I have hidden the unused options for the individual TextFields. <br />
For example, when &quot;Paragraph&quot; is selected, it doesnot make sense to have an option &quot;isDecimal&quot;, so it is hidden, and similarly for Number, Date, etc.			</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
	</td>
</tr>
